IDENTIFICATION DIVISION.
PROGRAM-ID. SimpleTextEditor.
AUTHOR. Simon Mikkelsen.
* This program is a simple text editor designed to showcase the elegance
* and grandeur of COBOL programming. It allows users to input text,
* store it, and display it back in a manner that is both delightful and
* enchanting. The program is a testament to the timeless beauty of COBOL.

ENVIRONMENT DIVISION.
CONFIGURATION SECTION.
INPUT-OUTPUT SECTION.
FILE-CONTROL.
    SELECT INPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'INPUT.TXT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.
    SELECT OUTPUT-FILE ASSIGN TO 'OUTPUT.TXT'
     ORGANIZATION IS LINE SEQUENTIAL.

DATA DIVISION.
FILE SECTION.
FD  INPUT-FILE.
01  INPUT-RECORD PIC X(80).

FD  OUTPUT-FILE.
01  OUTPUT-RECORD PIC X(80).

WORKING-STORAGE SECTION.
01  WS-USER-INPUT PIC X(80).
01  WS-TEMP-VAR PIC 9(4) VALUE 0.
01  WS-OVERFLOW-VAR PIC 9(2) VALUE 0.
01  WS-RAINY-DAY PIC X(80).
01  WS-SUNNY-DAY PIC X(80).
01  WS-UNUSED-VAR PIC X(10).

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
MAIN-PARA.
    DISPLAY "Welcome to the Simple Text Editor!"
    PERFORM INITIATE-FILES
    PERFORM GET-USER-INPUT
    PERFORM WRITE-TO-FILE
    PERFORM DISPLAY-FILE-CONTENT
    PERFORM CLOSE-FILES
    STOP RUN.

INITIATE-FILES.
    OPEN INPUT INPUT-FILE
    OPEN OUTPUT OUTPUT-FILE.

GET-USER-INPUT.
    DISPLAY "Please enter your text (max 80 characters):"
    ACCEPT WS-USER-INPUT
    MOVE WS-USER-INPUT TO WS-RAINY-DAY
    MOVE WS-USER-INPUT TO WS-SUNNY-DAY
    ADD 1 TO WS-OVERFLOW-VAR.

WRITE-TO-FILE.
    MOVE WS-RAINY-DAY TO OUTPUT-RECORD
    WRITE OUTPUT-RECORD.

DISPLAY-FILE-CONTENT.
    READ INPUT-FILE INTO WS-RAINY-DAY
     AT END DISPLAY "End of file reached."
    END-READ
    DISPLAY "The content of the file is:"
    DISPLAY WS-RAINY-DAY.

CLOSE-FILES.
    CLOSE INPUT-FILE
    CLOSE OUTPUT-FILE.

